{"product_id": "12120", "page": 10, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2018-02-05", "text": "This game still holds up today. Do yourself a favor and seek out the V1.0 \"downgrade\" (really it's an upgrade) and a handful of mods and you'll be playing a game that feels much newer than it actually is. Whether you want to go back to some nostalgia or just have an awesome game to play, San Andreas is a great option. Even in the first few hours of me playing the game again, I'm reminded of the countless things I'd forgotten. While it's not as polished as newer GTA entries, it feels like the team put a ton of work into making sure the game was full of things to do. Remember burglaries? I didn't. What about going and dancing? What about the infamous gang wars? There's so many side activities in the game, that San Andreas is the equivalent of three or four other games, all wrapped up in one budget-friendly package that'll run on practically any PC.", "hours": 7.6, "user_id": "76561198147896660", "username": "Vinny Scarletto", "products": 43, "early_access": false}
