{"product_id": "12120", "page": 258, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-01-29", "text": "Easily one of the best GTA's ever made. This game was one of the last GTA's to offer a true sandbox and roleplay experience with several side activies to boot. These features would be ethier very lacking or missing entierly in the major modern era GTA games (gta 4 and 5 respectivly) in comparison to San Andreas. While personally i like GTA 4's story more GTA San Andreas story is a close second. The only downside to the PC port is the controls are inverted in places they shouldn't be (the lowrider rythem minigame is a good example of this).\nOverall if you feel like playing one of the older GTA's start with this one as it's easily one of the best ones.", "hours": 4.2, "user_id": "76561198035121177", "username": "bigben115", "products": 302, "early_access": false}
