{"product_id": "12120", "page": 262, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-01-22", "text": "Updated : 20.12.2017.\nBoy. This game is by far the definitely my favorite GTA , and favorite game of all time. The music, the story, the nostalgia, the.... everything. Game is so perfect, and it has a lot of fun for 10 euros, which is definitely worth of . It's the best one in the series, and i have so many memories on it. Unfortunately, this game shows it's age on Windows 10, by having some issues, other than that, it works well without any predefined settings.\n1) Game crashes on startup often when you're trying to skip the intros. This isn't a big deal, because it's not game-breaking, and game can be started up normally when we ignore this issue.\n2) Weird textures. Graphics aren't bad for 2004 game (graphics don't matter to me anyway), but some player textures are weird and they look bad (i thought it was my contrast on display, but it was game's issue).\n3) Game hangs sometimes, i know i lost my progress on LS races, and now i have to do it again (RIP).\n4) Crashes sometimes, especially in the missions, but that is a rare case.\n5) Visible glitches, especially in the Smoke's crack palace, where it's obviously visible after the game is completed.\nSo, is this game worth buying ? Yes. I get often to rare problems with it, but it' 13 year old game, so i don't mind those bugs. Game is worth 10 eur indeed, since it has infinite replay value for me, and i'm huge GTA fan (i own all of them, excluding PSP ones, 1 and 2.). Game is really fun, and i really recommend it to everyone.", "hours": 124.8, "username": "Vatnaj\u00f6kkul", "products": 82, "found_funny": 12, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "12120", "page": 262, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-01-22", "text": "honestly one of the best gta games I have ever played if i had to rank games from 1 to 3 3 being not replayable and not interesting without any enhancing like mods and such i would rank 1: San Andreas 2: GTA IV 3: gta v. this game even though it is so old it still gets your attention with beautiful story and dialogue its overall just a masterpiece for rockstar.", "hours": 5.0, "username": "Caleb John", "products": 105, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "12120", "page": 262, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-01-22", "text": "Fantastic game and still holds up today. Huge map, lots of things to do. Wacky characters and more pop culture references you can shake a stick at.\nMy only problem with this particular release is that Rockstar have done nothing to modernise the game and simply re-released the PC port from over 10 years ago. Make sure you lock the frame-rate, and take time out to properly bind controls as this game was a pre-XInput release. Mouse controls are a bit janky as there's no lock-on mechanism and the mouse seems to have 'steps' when aiming making it much harder than the controller. A few more options to prevent the model and texture pop-in would have been nice too.", "hours": 6.8, "username": "Nerdbopper", "products": 248, "early_access": false}
