{"product_id": "12120", "page": 446, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-06-06", "text": "It surprised me that I still had fun with this game in 2016.\nBy this point in the GTA games, Rockstar had ironed out a lot of the annoying features and lack of features that characterized III and Vice City for me. The gameplay feels pretty good in regards to the driving and shooting which you'll be doing most of the time. The world is massive and there are places you'll never have to go but are still cool to visit. The story doesn't seem as good as Vice City's but it's definitely better than III's. The soundtrack is still amazing to me and the time period makes for cool continuity nods to the previous games. Even the cheats are improved with stuff like super punch and better flying cars.\nPick this game up if you had a good time with it in the past.", "hours": 44.3, "username": "UltimateXero", "products": 242, "early_access": false}
