{"product_id": "12120", "page": 455, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-05-14", "text": "Billy left his home with a dollar in his pocket and a head full of dreams. He said somehow, some way, its gotta get better than this. Patti packed her bags, left a note for her momma, she was just seventeen, There were tears in her eyes when she kissed her little sister goodbye. They held each other tight as they drove on through the night they were so exited. We got just one shot of life, lets take it while were still not afraid. Because life is so brief and time is a thief when youre undecided. And like a fistful of sand, it can slip right through your hands. Young hearts be free tonight.", "hours": 107.9, "username": "Naberius the Nefarious", "products": 107, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "12120", "page": 455, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-05-14", "text": "My first M rated game when I was but a wee lad. My dad's girlfriend bought this for me out of the eye of him, and I loved it. I played it, but never beat it.\nFast foward 7 years. I wanted to get my old Playstation 2 down and play some of my old games for nostalgia.\nIt's broken.\nI'm determined to play San Andreas again.\nMy birthday rolls around, I pick this up. So far I've binged 3 hours and it's just as fantastic as I remember it. Map is actually a lot smaller than my younger mind remembers it, but it's still fun nonetheless.\nFollowthedamntrain/10", "hours": 5.7, "username": "Crying", "products": 148, "found_funny": 6, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "12120", "page": 455, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-05-14", "text": "I just started playing GTA games in the past two years. I played the GTA games in order of their release date, going from GTA III to GTA V. I must say, even with all of the pros for GTA V, GTA San Andreas is much better than GTA V. Yes, the graphics are outdated, and yes, the map size is commparativly small, but I still find myself going back to play San Andreas just to free roam much more than V.\nFurthermore, the only GTA game that has a better story mode than San Andreas is GTA IV. (For those of you wondering GTA V has a commparativly horrible story mode.) For instance, whe I had to kill Big Smoke, I had a lot of internal conflict. I didn't want to kill him, but he was an \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665, so when I had to kill him, I almost couldn't bring myself to do it. There are many instances where this type of confict or something similar occurs, making this game's storyline one of the best GTA storyline son existance.\nNo, I'm not a nostalgic filled GTA San Andreas fan and no, I do not think GTA V is the best GTA game in existance. On the chance that I am starting to sound like Sammyclassicsonicfan, play some of the classic GTA games, including IV, and then reconsider your opinion on both San Andreas AND V.", "hours": 9.4, "username": "Sainta Claws", "products": 85, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
