{"product_id": "12120", "page": 458, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-05-08", "text": "GTA: San Andreas.. A game that opened up a lot of enjoyable and memorable moments. I remember being by the coast and a blonde woman in roller skates flying past me saying \"I'm so thick that I can\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665quot;, I cried away at this for quite a while and never forgot it. This game exposed what was supposed to be the life of a drug dealer and the struggles that came for Carl Johnson. Playing this on the PS2 was great simply because I would have one of my friends play with me, the coop was a great idea which I loved after playing this alone which would get pretty boring. The missions were very fun and exciting; moments of rage were present very frequently when I failed.", "hours": 7.0, "username": "jonmac5037", "products": 82, "early_access": false}
