{"product_id": "12120", "page": 532, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-12-05", "text": "Bought San Andreas on the recent Exploration Sale. Runs bordered even at native resolution. Rockstar still didn't fixed the widescreen issue, the game looks stretched either vertically or horizontally, depending on your in-game setting. I can accept such issues from Delta Force games, seeing as they're older, but Not from GTA games, because Rockstar clearly has the resources to fix these issues, but doesn't have the will to update the games that basically made the company. Which is a damn shame.\nEDIT: changed the rating to positive, because some things work better now, the game is more playable. Still bitter about cut content.", "hours": 7.3, "username": "1singur", "products": 322, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "12120", "page": 532, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-12-05", "text": "My actual playtime for this game is off-record, based off of the years I spent on it via disk when I didn't actually own Steam.\nI would say 300+ hours playtime.\nSan Andreas remains to be my favourite of the series.\n- Great story, great music.\n- Full character customisation\n- The map is gloriously huge, with 3 different ambient settings\n- Huge variety of side quests and tasks\n- Character skill building via gym. RPG element is GO.\nK-Rose remains to be my favourite radio station. Everyone else in my house as a child hated K-Rose.\nOr at least my singing to K-Rose. Or maybe it was just repeating the whole thing over and over in a badly imitated accent, including the pool table birth part.\nOne of my favourite things to do was see how many vehicles I could destroy by parking my car in the middle of the road and shooting the gas tank. You'd be surprised how many people need eye tests. I swear another 10 cars would drive right into that thing without stopping.\nBest way to make cash, ever.\nThe 5-star police chases when I flew my plane over area 69, resulting in a hasty parachute down in a complete panic, were intense.\nOne of the most comfortable games to play ever. If you haven't tried GTA before, I recommend playing this one before GTA V.", "hours": 155.2, "username": "Roopoo", "products": 706, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
