{"product_id": "12120", "page": 552, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-10-29", "text": "This game has so many activities...\nTo name a few, you could\n- Hunt down and kill some drug dealers\n- Play bar games such as pool, blackjack etc\n- Become a Police Officer, Medic or Taxi Driver\n- Find Bigfoot\n- Buy a house to save your game and store your weapons\n- Get a girlfriend, and then reach max relationship to unlock new outfits and bonuses\n- Go inside the hundreds of enterable buildings, such as police stations\n- Rob a house and sell the product\n- Buy some new clothes\n- Take over some gang territories\n- Recruit some of your gang and cause havoc\n- Go to the gym\n- Get fat, slim or muscular (the character actually becomes fat, slim or muscular)\nThere is much more to do than GTA V, not even counting the 99 story missions and countless random events/side missions, if you can look past the obvious graphical age.\nOh and I almost forgot,\nI'll have two number 9s, a number 9 large, a number 6 with extra dip, a number 7, two number 45s, one with cheese, and a large soda.", "hours": 51.4, "user_id": "76561198251314460", "username": "BoxFacedGaming", "products": 7, "early_access": false}
