{"product_id": "12120", "page": 737, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-01", "text": "Thank goodness they updated this broken classic!\nNo longer will we be troubled with video option menus cluttered by obscure resolutions that nobody uses like 1920x1080 or anything in 16:10!. Replay your favorite game in glorious \"2 generations ago console-vision\"(tm) featuring random glitches and missing textures! Swoon at \"now sort of supports the XBox 360 pad, kinda\" functionality! The newly revamped soundtrack has even been slimmed down by 18  or so songs making it much sleeker and streamlined!\nDo you frequently shake with impotent rage knowing that some people like playing this game with mods? Well shake no more! All mods are dead!\nPlay it again for the first time, your old saves are no good! This is the definitive version! Buy it! Make alternate accounts and buy it for them too!", "hours": 0.9, "username": "Underwhelmed", "products": 940, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "12120", "page": 737, "page_order": 2, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-12-01", "text": "In October San Andreas became 10 years old. I replayed it because of nostalgia and I was shockingly surprised to see that a big part of its soundtrack was removed (18 songs = 11% of the total number of songs if my information is correct). And I felt it while progressing through the game. Towards the end I was flipping radio channels to get a song I haven't heard that much and it was becoming increasingly difficult to do so.\nEven though I enjoyed it, I can't recommend it. Not like this. This recent patch which did more damage than improvements (the game crashed a few times for me but usually it ran ok).\nIf you want an old school GTA game, get Vice City. It has better mission structure and a better world (SA has a bigger world and a better setting for a GTA game but it doesn't use it as well as Vice City did).", "hours": 30.0, "user_id": "76561197992626658", "username": "Tze", "products": 367, "early_access": false}
