{"product_id": "12120", "page": 765, "page_order": 5, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-11-07", "text": "Once upon a time, this was fun PC port of a landmark console title.\nThen November 7, 2014 (Black Friday) came.\nRockstar \"patched\" all the life out of the title, effectively replacing the PC version with a port of the mobile version.  With that, even users who had purchased the game long ago are now stuck with an even poorer port of the game, fewer songs in the game's soundtrack, and paltry graphics/resolution options.\nRockstar has perfectly exploited and demonstrated all of the real and perceived flaws of a digital distribution platform.  And they wonder why people might opt to pirate games still?", "hours": 3.9, "user_id": "76561197973410452", "username": "Sponge-worthy", "products": 225, "found_funny": 2, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "12120", "page": 765, "page_order": 6, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-11-07", "text": "GTA San Andreas in general is a classic game no doubt, but this release is truly a horrible port. It took nearly 10 years for Rockstar to add true controller support (November 2014) and even that is mediocre at best. It's worthy to note that in the November 2014 patch, Rockstar disenfranchised its current customers by unnecessarily removing content and apparently stripping out higher resolutions options. The patch also caused the in-game graphics to appear worse (though this could just be isolated to my experience). Overall, the steam version of GTA San Andreas is more like the \"Frankenstein version\u201d and I wouldn't recommend it to those seeking the authentic GTA San Andreas experience. If you don't mind your game constantly transforming on you, then I suppose this version may be for you. Rockstar's track record of poor GTA PC releases undoubtedly continues with their latest revision of this great game.\nFor those who already own GTA: San Andreas on Steam, you should consider installing \"Grand Theft Auto: San Andreas - Enhanced Edition\" mod per the Steam User Guide:\n. You will not be disappointed in this mod as it will make your GTA San Andreas experience on the PC much more tolerable and playable!", "hours": 23.6, "username": "jerms819", "products": 26, "found_funny": 3, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "12120", "page": 765, "page_order": 7, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-11-07", "text": "Because the patch from the 7th November 2014 removed 18(!) songs from the game. It was a forced update to all who paid for this game. Better try to get an older retail version and do not buy the game here.", "hours": 1.9, "username": "Emily Howard", "products": 600, "found_funny": 13, "early_access": false}
