{"product_id": "12120", "page": 774, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-10-20", "text": "===WARNING SPOILERS BELOW DO NOT READ IF YOU DON'T WANT THE PLOT TO BE SPOILED===\nGrand Thegt Auto is a game developed by ME  at my house in 2006. IT's a flash indie game made with the source engine and it has cross compatability with both lindows and windux. Right off the bat you are thrust into the shoes of Coldsteel the gang banger aka Carl Johntron working for the illuminati fish capers known as CRASH who are corrupt and work to further the secret agenda of single black women everywhere. After a plane crash the preisdent calls in Chill iron to come sell drugs to kids across california so CRASH can operate in secret and save the world from the russian mobsters importing illegal lobsters to suburban housewives in the US. But the game takes a twist when Icemetal the gang banger is thrown in crime for a prison he did not commet. His brother Small Vapor turns out to be working with the russians and you must break out of prison using your streeet knowledge to board a giant airship made of lobsters and kill your brother. Afterwards you are shown a cutscene where your mother turns out to be a lobster and you kill yourself wiht your brothers corpse due to your grief. If you get the bad end then CRASH loses all their funding and the russians ivnade us and the cold war breaks out. There is no good end yet because I haven't got it yet. 7/10", "hours": 30.8, "username": "Duffy Moon", "products": 577, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "12120", "page": 774, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-10-20", "text": "I've never finished this game, but damn have I wanted to.\nThis game is probably the longest base game I've never actually finished. Granted, I probably would have finished it if my laptop hadn't crashed, therefore destroying all my game, and making me have to restart from the beginning again.\nBut I'm actually glad that happened. Because this game is so damn good it deserves two playthroughs, hell it probably deserves five. It's definitely the long cherished gem of the GTA series for a reason, whilst the much heralded GTA IV might beat it on gameplay depth, GTA: San Andreas sure as hell beats it on everything else.", "hours": 59.4, "username": "buttons15", "products": 192, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
