{"product_id": "12120", "page": 814, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-28", "text": "I'm playing through this game despite how I despise hip-hop and gang culture. It's not really that the game glorifies or is critical of the material anyway.. it just reflects on it and lets the player decide, and it's not without its humor.\nBut when the main character indulges requests to kill complete strangers because some idiot he doesen't even respect asks him to, it comes across as totally inconsistent, makes no sense for the story, and seems dumb. Hopefully that won't be the rest of the missions to the game, which is probably massively long. I bet i'm 2% done or something, ugh.\nThis is one of the better GTA games of all time. It's dated today.. so i guess you would need to turn the clock back too far to play this one, unless you really want to go back and try it.", "hours": 7.3, "user_id": "76561197963217574", "username": "Justice Ftw", "products": 166, "early_access": false}
