{"product_id": "12120", "page": 850, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-04-03", "text": "ohh man i used to play this game when i was a kid.This is the real best GTA game of all times its has a lot of options you can do like in RL. like killing some Ballas,havingfun,Mafiafight,Racing,Robbing,Dancing and more...\nfrom me to you guys. you probably should return to play this game its perfect for having fun like\n1.using cheats\n2.kicking some Ballas\n3.making Riot around San Andreas like a Boss\n4.also customize cars and racing for fun\nThis is the perfect GTA game for Everything you allways wanted to do :)\nRating:10/10", "hours": 113.7, "username": "LombaXShade", "products": 803, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "12120", "page": 850, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-04-03", "text": "Have you ever wondered what it's like being a gangbanger? Did you ever ponder whether the pigs who stole your money have been in collaboration with your homies who  may now have cause to betray you? Are you a lunatic? Would you like to be one?\nIf you've answered yes to any of the above questions then GTA: San Andreas might be right for you.\nThis game is full of gangbanging, chola craziness, big black men ordering everything off the menu, freebird, compton, grove street. Not to mention: skydiving, plane robbing, house burgling, faggio riding, liberty city visiting, heists, casinos, oysters, horseshoes, plantation farming: you name it.\nIs this game right for you?  Will you love it? In the words of the wise Big Smoke:\n\"All we had to do was follow the damn train\"  - which of course is referring to the philosophical insight that we must all follow the damn train or we will become lost on the wrong side of the tracks.", "hours": 96.2, "username": "K.Ev", "products": 146, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "12120", "page": 850, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-04-02", "text": "Awsome game, it has improves so much, after turning 3d, Now you can explore massive junk of land, some times it feels almoust too big. Main improvment in this game is movement, you can move more freely in this game than older ones. This GTA is focused heavily on costumizing. You can change your character looks(pretty massivly i would say) and first time in GTA series Car tuning. There are also lot of easter eggs, and fun vehicles, like Monster Quarry truck, atv, Hovercraft, Karts and more. I liked it and reccomend it.\nOlny bad moment is sometimes your mouse stop working, but you can fix this, by opening steam in game window", "hours": 28.6, "user_id": "76561198001234825", "username": "Jyrka", "products": 213, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "12120", "page": 850, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-04-02", "text": "This game has alot of fun aspects and a great storyline, would recommend to anyone who likes driving,shooting, chasing, flying, 90s music. Also cluckin bell.\nGTA San Andreas. The 5th main installment of the Grand Theft Auto series and perhaps the most ambitious one of them all.\nThis game always put quantity and size over graphics and focus- and it pays off beautifully.\nUnlike most of the GTA titles, this game includes an entire sprawling state for it's map as opposed to one city, including three large cities, plenty of villages and towns, a mountain range, forests, deserts, canyons, rivers, airports and also comes with plenty of restaurants, including the infamous Cluckin' Bell.\nIf the giant and diverse world isn't enough for you, perhaps the addition of dozens of miscellaneous missions, jobs, car races, along with the potential to master your skill at arms or on the road or air would suffice.\nThe main quest also holds up additionally, bringing the player all the way around the world and eventually back to where they started off- and Rockstar made sure to include any action desires one would dream of.\nDO play this game. It's legendary.", "hours": 389.3, "username": "Maximus IV", "products": 58, "early_access": false}
