{"product_id": "12120", "page": 853, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-03-23", "text": "What can I say that hasn't been said? It's Grand Theft Auto: San Andreas. One of the most legendary, historic games in existence. It takes all of the beloved features of the GTA franchise and spices it up, adding loads of customization to your character (CJ) and all the cars you can find on the street. The atmosphere is even better, set in an early 1990s Los Santos (obviously based off of Los Angeles). The graphics can look a little pixelated in today's age, which is understandable, seeing as how this game is about a decade old now. Still a classic. Still highly recommended. 10/10", "hours": 12.8, "username": "Retro Renegade", "products": 847, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "12120", "page": 853, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-03-23", "text": "WASD! Responsive controls, good action, smooth animations.\nPvP features a 4v4v4 layout with a few different maps that change node layouts to cap flags / gather resources on. Interesting concept that leaves your team learning when exactly to give and take.\n2 PvE modes including Horde Mode and Scout Missions with multiple locations / reward tiers / boss battles that offer good replayability. Gotta beat that clock!\nClassic infected characters from the Dead Island series that we all love, including the Butcher and Ram.\n4 characters currently now with ultimate abilities and individual persistent leveling. Characters feel unique and BALANCED, but would like to see more variety similar to the ones in alpha.\nAccount leveling / workbench leveling now implemented to let you craft higher tiered weapons and increase character strength. Workbench also now lets you use gold to easily craft weapon blueprints you have without having all of the required materials.\nF2P! As of this post nothing in the shop that breaks gameplay so that is a huge plus.\nGame is constantly being updated and some core features have changed drastically since then so my review may differ.", "hours": 0.1, "username": "Yippee-ki-yay, motherfucker", "products": 182, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "12120", "page": 853, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-03-23", "text": "Best GTA Ever! It's hard in certain parts but the amazing gameplay and story make for an extremely fun game 11/10", "hours": 69.0, "username": "red backpack guy", "products": 126, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "12120", "page": 854, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-03-23", "text": "WASD! Responsive controls, good action, smooth animations.\nPvP features a 4v4v4 layout with a few different maps that change node layouts to cap flags / gather resources on. Interesting concept that leaves your team learning when exactly to give and take.\n2 PvE modes including Horde Mode and Scout Missions with multiple locations / reward tiers / boss battles that offer good replayability. Gotta beat that clock!\nClassic infected characters from the Dead Island series that we all love, including the Butcher and Ram.\n4 characters currently now with ultimate abilities and individual persistent leveling. Characters feel unique and BALANCED, but would like to see more variety similar to the ones in alpha.\nAccount leveling / workbench leveling now implemented to let you craft higher tiered weapons and increase character strength. Workbench also now lets you use gold to easily craft weapon blueprints you have without having all of the required materials.\nF2P! As of this post nothing in the shop that breaks gameplay so that is a huge plus.\nGame is constantly being updated and some core features have changed drastically since then so my review may differ.", "hours": 0.1, "username": "Yippee-ki-yay, motherfucker", "products": 182, "early_access": false}
