{"product_id": "12120", "page": 854, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-03-22", "text": "Simply a masterpiece\nWhile the graphics are dated (they didn't look so great even for the time), this game has a legacy of narrative and gameplay exellence, making it the finest installment in an already amazing series.\nThere's too much to talk about in one review, since there's simply so much to do in a large world such as San Andreas. This game will keep you hooked to it for years and years to come, and that's not even including the amazing story, which has been and still is the pinnacle of Video game narrative. If you're reading this review column to decide on whether or not to buy this game. Stop reading and just buy it now. It's one of the greatest games feats of the modern gaming generation.", "hours": 320.4, "username": "Frapple", "products": 190, "early_access": false}
