{"product_id": "12120", "page": 881, "page_order": 5, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-01-19", "text": "Did not work for the loongest time, but when it does work its extremely slow and unresponsive. Control bindings are not meant to be for PC, even if you change them, you cant manipulate the camera in any way and there is no use of the mouse during gameplay. I like GTA San Andreas but definatly not for the PC. In my opinion, a waste of money. If you're going to buy it, get it for the xbox or playstation.", "hours": 1.1, "username": "PrometheusTheCreator", "products": 39, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "12120", "page": 881, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-19", "text": "Love this game brings back so many memorys", "hours": 11.4, "username": "Goku Black", "products": 163, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "12120", "page": 881, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-19", "text": "I absoluetely love this game. It is still my favorite GTA by far, so it has been fun to go on a little nostalgia trip. It feels like it has ported really well to PC for the most part, it still has the same feel and enjoyment of running around doing missions, exploring the city, or just running around causing mayhem. My only issue is that the controls for me do not seem to have ported very well, I have spent a lot of time re-configuring controls over and even then there were a few controls that felt a little wonky. The first low rider mission is an example of this where it felt a little odd, but with a little re-configuration I was able to finish the mission and continue enjoying myself. Overall, this was not enough for me to not recommend this game. I would especially recommend it for those who are fans of the series and those who love this particular game in the series.", "hours": 8.6, "user_id": "76561198050094299", "username": "Sicle_Mince", "products": 384, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "12120", "page": 881, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-19", "text": "If I was allowed this as a kid, I would have said something like, \"Game of my childhood\" or \"PS2 memories relieved\" or maybe even \"I literally coughed up a lung when I saw this on steam.\" but I didn't get this game as a kid, but that void was filled with Simpsons Hit & Run. But now that I've played it (10 years later), I'm a bit late with my conversations about it that should have happened in the playground at primary school and not in high school. But as a game it is an amazing experience only a few things bother me, like the way you are thrown from your bike when you hit a lamp post, the way the characters mouths down move (doesn't bother as much because it was made in '04) and the lack of a Steam Workshop. Great game. 10/10. Best substitute for GTA V on PC.", "hours": 23.3, "username": "milksnatcher_thatcher79", "products": 193, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "12120", "page": 881, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-19", "text": "i recently strated playing san andreas and ive relized that its much better than the current gta games due to its great campain and addicting freeroam. and most people will say that gta4 is better but no its not san andreas feels a lot more like a true freeroam game and you know who doesnt love a game with a awsome soundtrack and npcs dressed like elvis!", "hours": 27.7, "username": "Scar-20", "products": 91, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "12120", "page": 882, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-19", "text": "Rockstar did not slack off making this one. I'm really impressed with the effort that has been put into the game details even having different maneuverability for each type of car and the planes, the choppers, the boats - everything! There's also a lot to do and a fairly huge area to explore which for me is just about right as opposed to later GTAs with bigger game worlds (its dragging sometimes). I like how each area has a different aura to it making you feel like you're playing a different game and story for each. The only cons I have about this game is that sometimes I get crashes and there is an issue with the game resolution being unable to match max monitor setting. Anyways, I highly recommend this game! If you're a serious gamer, make sure you don't pass this one. Great story, fun and challenging missions and light game atmosphere.", "hours": 115.1, "username": "rjrad", "products": 690, "early_access": false}
