{"product_id": "12120", "page": 903, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-14", "text": "A pure and simple classical. Way better than GTA IV if you ask me! I can't tell how much time I spent on this fabulous game - I at least spent ten times what Steam is telling - and I never been disapointed.\nThere's some bugs with the mouse don't working, since the game is hardly compatible with multicores, but it's easy to fix: just set a single core on it in the Task Manager. Also, a little minus: no windowed mod, except by downloading a dll. If you need it, just tell me and I'll give you.\nStill, the game is totally worth it despite those two defects. Awesome story, nice jokes, plenty of craziness; I love it!\n9/10", "hours": 46.1, "username": "Nerubian Squirrel", "products": 609, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "12120", "page": 903, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-14", "text": "Even if the Grand Theft Auto series has always been good, this was one of the best games in the series. In many people's opinion it was better than GTA IV. Although it wasn't perfect, the sheer size of San Andreas was something that could not be denied. It had country sides and even the city of Los Santos. This was R* (Rockstar's) best game until GTA V.\nEven thought GTA: SA is old I still enjoy playing it and it's still  great game. The story is great and the open-world is fun too. I highly recommend it.\n(it's better than minecraft)", "hours": 34.0, "user_id": "76561198057198704", "username": "Volca", "products": 83, "early_access": false}
