{"product_id": "12120", "page": 907, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-07", "text": "An Amazing game. Both on a technical (at least for it's time) level, and on a gameplay level. It's a huge world, and entire state, with 3 large cities and 12 small towns. It always feels fresh, and the random events caused by the AI are just sweet. I poured at least 30 hours on the Xbox Live Arcade version, and I never even left the first city. It's pretty much the best PS2 gen GTA there is.", "hours": 11.7, "user_id": "76561198048402595", "username": "Maakat", "products": 282, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "12120", "page": 907, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-07", "text": "Grand Theft Auto: San Andreas is a fun single player game where it is taken place in San Andreas in the 90's. Your character is a young aferican american man named Cj who meets up with his old gang and wants to take back what was once their's! Now in San Andreas you can play missions which is mostly the story to the game, or you can just run around and shoot and steal stuff! You can swim where most of the other GTA's you couldn't. You can also fly airplanes, jets, fighter jets, and not sure but I think helicopters too. Also the this is one of the GTA's where you can pilot a airplanes which is one reason why I bought this game. If you like good story lines or just like to mess around this is so the game for you!", "hours": 283.4, "user_id": "76561198078555543", "username": "NavySealGuy1001", "products": 62, "early_access": false}
