{"product_id": "12120", "page": 913, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-25", "text": "This is a great game.  They fixed all of the problems with the previous two 3-d Grand Theft Auto games.  It's fun, some frustrating missions but when you beat them there's a sense of accomplishment.\nThen you get to the flying missions.  Did anyone play test these missions?  They're \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665ing impossible.  The controls are complete\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665  Like many people, my San Andreas experience comes to an unsatisfying dead stop at these mandatory flying missions.  If it weren't for the flying missions, I'd give the game a nine.  But as it stands:\nPwninator Score: 6/10", "hours": 37.9, "username": "Pwny McPwnPwn", "products": 65, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "12120", "page": 913, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-24", "text": "This game can't be bypassed. With its funny sense of humor that Rockstar's known for, awesome gameplay, great modding community that is still somewhat active, GTA's FIRST black character, and huge map, I give it a 9/10. DO NOT, AND I MEAN DO NOT, PASS THIS GAME.", "hours": 155.4, "username": "White Mango", "products": 211, "early_access": false}
