{"product_id": "12120", "page": 920, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-09-05", "text": "Many years later, this continues to be my favorite Grand Theft Auto game. The game world (especially at the time) was absolutely massive and spanned 3 (or four depending on how you're counting) different regions with full-sized cities. It has quasi-RPG elements allowing you to alter your appearance based on how you eat and work out, as well as gaining skill in driving. Then there was a massive amount of different missions, side missions, activities, etc. so that it always seemed there was something more to do. I've lost a large chunk of my personal time to this game and I keep coming back to it even now. Can't recommend enough.", "hours": 54.4, "username": "Bo Steed", "products": 581, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "12120", "page": 920, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-09-05", "text": "Magnicifent game. Simply a blast to play. I can't believe all the time I have spent playing this game it's astounding. Revisiting this game many years after it came out turned out to be very interesting. This game was truly ahead of it's time and on it's own level. A masterpiece 10/10", "hours": 71.7, "user_id": "76561198008855170", "username": "Esoteric_Templar", "products": 86, "early_access": false}
