{"product_id": "12120", "page": 949, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-11-25", "text": "There is nothing quite like soaring over Las Venturas in a Hydra jump-jet to the tune of Billy Idol's White Wedding... ah nostalgia.\n\nThis will always be one of my favourite toys.\nI haven't viewed San Andreas as a 'game' for many years, though it is a very good one by most counts, IF (and its a big 'if') you can ignore/tollerate the disgraceful language, sex and drug references.\nDespite the vulgar reputation of the series, GTA:SA will always be one of the most prized jewels in my collection for its unmatchable sandbox beauty.\nThis is a must have in my opinion. A true gaming classic.", "hours": 34.8, "username": "itsDVarin", "products": 370, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "12120", "page": 949, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2012-11-23", "text": "EDIT AS OF NOVEMBER 2014: DO NOT BUY THIS GAME ON STEAM. THERE IS REMOVED MUSIC FROM THE RADIO STATIONS AND OTHER CONTENT!!!\nThis game is pure gold, and a classic. From great graphics to gameplay to music on the radiostations to everything. Hell, what can I say? Everyone has played San Andreas. All I can say, is that you shouldn't buy the Steam version of GTA: SA unless you're only buying it for the single player. If get the non-steam version and downgrade it to 1.0 (which is unfortunetly slightly buggier) then you're able to use more mods for the game\nAs well as using San Andreas Multiplayer (SAMP) Yes, that's right! You can play multiplayer for san andreas! I highly recommend playing on UIF which is a free roam server and you can spawn (almost) whatever you want  and go flying at top speed across the entire map! It's great fun.", "hours": 170.7, "username": "Dalek:.", "products": 373, "early_access": false}
