{"product_id": "12120", "page": 984, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2011-05-21", "text": "The developer issued a patch (all these years later) that TAKES OUT content from the game (17 songs, 1080p resolution, surround sound and more). It's the most unethical act from a big publisher I've ever seen here on Steam. This breaks consumer laws in most countries, and it's basically an illegal act. Shame on Rockstar (never buying any of their products anymore) and on Valve for allowing developers do this.", "hours": 132.1, "username": "Cervantes", "products": 212, "early_access": false}
